      <description>You must be very happy after the construction of your storage shed. It must be really good based on the right garden storage shed plans you have chosen. All the items are ready to go inside. Absolutely, it feels great &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://gardenstorageshedplans.com/learn-some-proper-maintenance-for-storage-sheds/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/garden-storage-shed-plans/GARDEN_STORAGE_SHED_PLANS-Learn_Some_Proper_Maintenance_for_Storage_Sheds.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>You must be very happy after the construction of your storage shed. It must be really good based on the right <strong><a href="http://gardenstorageshedplans.com/recommend/" target="_blank">garden storage shed plans</a></strong> you have chosen. All the items are ready to go inside. Absolutely, it feels great to see that finally, every tool and stuff have its own neat place in the shed. The next thing you need to learn is how to protect your investment so that it can serve you for many years. <strong>Garden shed plans</strong> are really very helpful in making projects successfully, but without proper maintenance, anything you build will tear and wear sooner than you have expected.</p>
<p>Let the following measures for storage shed maintenance be your guide.</p>
<p><strong>Paint Your Shed</strong></p>
<p>Before you put anything in your storage shed; be sure to paint it to protect and give it a nice look. Paint is good on wood (and other materials used on sheds as well) as shield against environmental elements that can cause damage. You can try to use good quality paint to avoid repainting often so that you can save time and money. Varnish is ideal on wood to keep the charm that wood provides in any surrounding.<strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>Take Care of the Roof</strong></p>
<p>Check the roof regularly for loose shingles and signs of leak because leaks may damage the precious things you keep inside and the wood itself when left for a long time. Take all dirt, dry leaves and twigs out from the roof as they will cause corrosion and rust if not removed. It doesn’t matter how you do the repair. For some, the easiest way is to replace loose or lost shingles, and then apply some quality roof coating to finish the job.</p>
<p><strong>Check the different Hardware</strong></p>
<p>It’s normal to see loose hardware like nails, bolts and screws. After a month or so, some kinds of wood would relax and make some tightly fastened hardware loose. You can drive the nails back and retighten the screws in place or replace them with new ones. Check the door fasteners, hinges, bolts and screws often to prevent the door from sagging. You can use grease or oil to prevent fasteners and hinges from rust.</p>
<p><strong>Keep Pests Away</strong></p>
<p>The most common pest that can invade your beautiful storage shed is the termites. They can quickly make your wooden shed their home and cause irreparable damage to the wood before you even know it. Discard pieces wood and dead plants out of your yard because these are favorite food for termites. They will surely find their way to your storage shed when eating these materials. Use termite resistant materials in making a ramp for your shed like pressure treated wood or steel. Rats are also frequent visitors in isolated  rooms like storage sheds. Treat them with the right rat pesticides.</p>
<p>It’s not enough that you have found the best <strong>garden storage shed plans</strong> that meet your taste and build a beautiful shed that you can be proud off. You can work on wood and build your shed in less time and cost, but you also have to learn the appropriate methods of maintenance to make it stand the test of time. Of course, you don’t have to go far when you have found your <strong>garden shed plans</strong> from My Shed Plans; you’ll find tips for maintenance too.</p>
<p><strong><a href="http://gardenstorageshedplans.com/recommend/" target="_blank">Click here for garden storage shed plans and maintenance tips.</a></strong></p>
]]></content:encoded>
